Redeemer’s College of Technology and Management, Ogun State, has said it will produce 92 graduates in its forthcoming convocation. A statement by the school said the mission of the proprietor of RECTEM,  Pastor Enoch Adeboye, was to present to labour market high quality, knowledgeable and innovative graduates worthy in skills and character. Rector of RECTEM, Dr Stella Mofunaya noted that the second convocation would hold on Friday, April 8, 2022, at the RCCG Youth Centre, Lagos-Ibadan Express Way, Redemption Camp, Ogun State. She added that though the faith-based private polytechnic was young, it had made tremendous academic progress as well as numerical growth since its inception in 2017. “RECTEM, a trail-blazer in raising champions with the mission to produce high quality, knowledgeable and innovative graduates worthy in skills and character, who will become first-class professionals in the fields of science, technology, and management. “We will not rest on our oars in giving the best to our students. “We are glad to inform you that our graduates are not only academically fit, but they are also entrepreneurially solid, ready to create employment as they all have been empowered with one skill or the other in line with TVET goals.” Rector mentioned that the school had high hope in the graduates, saying they would impact their generation positively.  All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com